  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">FAO Emergency and Early Action Support to Affected Communities caused by Drought conditions in Lesotho</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this FAO project is to improve the availability of food in the short term and avert a major food insecurity situation following various climate related shocks. FAO will provide 22,000 households with home gardening kits to allow for a diversification of household level nutrition and wheat seeds to support the winter cropping period. FAO will also support 11,870 small holder farmers with fodder seeds and vaccinations of 570,000 livestock. Some132,187 individuals will be supported over 6 months.</narrative>
  </description>
